  "meta_commentary": "Execute in deployable slices, not as one risky production flip. Build schema and pure planning first, then shadow integration, then authoritative side effects, then final cleanup. The most important implementation traps are shadow accidentally mutating state, route keys accidentally creating multiple pool budgets, and final cleanup being applied before the production observation gates. Keep the approved plan's distinction between pool-scoped capacity and route-scoped backoff visible in every review.",
